An accident involving a truck around Upper-Iweka, Onitsha in Anambra State, has led to the death of a pedestrian. State Commander of the Federal Road Safety Corps, Andrew Kumapayi, confirmed the incident to the News Agency of Nigeria on Friday in Awka. Kumapayi said the accident, which occurred at 03:20 p.m., was attributed to the violation of speed limit and loss of control. He said, “The fatal crash involving a Mack Truck with registration number DGE352XA was caused by speed limit violation and loss of control. “According to an eyewitness, the truck lost control after the MCC pedestrian bridge and fell into the adjoining gutter, killing a pedestrian.” Kumapayi, who said that the scene had been cleared, advised motorists to drive within stipulated speed limits and shun all forms of reckless driving that could only lead to avoidable road mishaps. (NAN)